label.value: BMP signaling pathway involved in ureter morphogenesis

definition.value: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of a member of the BMP (bone morphogenetic protein) family to a receptor on the surface of a target cell, which contributes to the shaping of the ureter. The ureter is a tube that extends from the kidney to the bladder.

label.value: BMP signaling pathway involved in renal system segmentation

definition.value: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of a member of the BMP (bone morphogenetic protein) family to a receptor on the surface of a target cell, which contributes to the segmentation of the renal system.

label.value: mRNA destabilization

definition.value: Any process that decreases the stability of an mRNA molecule, making it more vulnerable to degradative processes. Messenger RNA is the intermediate molecule between DNA and protein. It includes UTR and coding sequences. It does not contain introns.

label.value: 3'-UTR-mediated mRNA destabilization

definition.value: An mRNA destabilization process in which one or more RNA-binding proteins associate with the 3'-untranslated region (UTR) of an mRNA.

label.value: type I terminal bouton

definition.value: Terminal inflated portion of the axon of a glutamatergic neuron, containing the specialized apparatus necessary to release neurotransmitters that will induce the contraction of muscle. The axon terminus is considered to be the whole region of thickening and the terminal bouton is a specialized region of it.

label.value: type II terminal bouton

definition.value: Terminal inflated portion of the axon of a non-glutamatergic neuron, containing the specialized apparatus necessary to release neurotransmitters at a regulatory synapse. The axon terminus is considered to be the whole region of thickening and the terminal bouton is a specialized region of it.

label.value: type Ib terminal bouton

definition.value: Terminal inflated portion of the axon of a glutamatergic neuron, containing the specialized apparatus necessary for the tonic release neurotransmitters that will induce the contraction of muscle. Type Ib terminal boutons are larger than type Is terminal boutons.

label.value: type Is terminal bouton

definition.value: Terminal inflated portion of the axon of a glutamatergic neuron, containing the specialized apparatus necessary for the phasic release neurotransmitters that will induce the contraction of muscle. Type Is terminal boutons are smaller than type Ib terminal boutons.

label.value: negative regulation of chromatin silencing at silent mating-type cassette

definition.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate, or extent of chromatin silencing at silent mating-type cassette. Chromatin silencing at silent mating-type cassette is the repression of transcription at silent mating-type loci by altering the structure of chromatin.

label.value: regulation of chromatin silencing at rDNA

definition.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the repression of transcription of ribosomal DNA by altering the structure of chromatin.

label.value: negative regulation of chromatin silencing at rDNA

definition.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the repression of transcription of ribosomal DNA by altering the structure of chromatin.

label.value: clathrin-sculpted gamma-aminobutyric acid transport vesicle

definition.value: A clathrin-sculpted lipid bilayer membrane-enclosed vesicle after clathrin release and containing gamma-aminobutyric acid transport vesicle.

label.value: clathrin-sculpted gamma-aminobutyric acid transport vesicle lumen

definition.value: The volume enclosed by the membrane of the clathrin-sculpted gamma-aminobutyric acid transport vesicle.

label.value: clathrin-sculpted gamma-aminobutyric acid transport vesicle membrane

definition.value: The lipid bilayer surrounding a clathrin-sculpted gamma-aminobutyric acid transport vesicle.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter involved in mesonephros development

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter that contributes to the mesonephros progressing from its initial formation to the mature state.

label.value: BMP signaling pathway involved in heart development

definition.value: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of a member of the BMP (bone morphogenetic protein) family to a receptor on the surface of a target cell, which contributes to the progression of the heart over time.

label.value: BMP signaling pathway involved in Malpighian tubule cell chemotaxis

definition.value: A series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of a member of the BMP (bone morphogenetic protein) family to a receptor on the surface of a target cell, which contributes to the directed movement of a Malpighian tubule cell toward a stimulus, thereby contributing to the shaping of the tubule.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to osmotic stress

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a stimulus indicating an increase or decrease in the concentration of solutes outside the organism or cell.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to osmotic stress

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a stimulus indicating an increase or decrease in the concentration of solutes outside the organism or cell.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to arsenic-containing substance

definition.value: Modulation of the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of an arsenic stimulus from compounds containing arsenic, including arsenates, arsenites, and arsenides.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to arsenic-containing substance

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of an arsenic stimulus from compounds containing arsenic, including arsenates, arsenites, and arsenides.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to copper ion

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter in response to an copper ion stimulus.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to copper ion

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter in response to an copper ion stimulus.

label.value: negative regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to copper ion

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter in response to an copper ion stimulus.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to cobalt ion

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter in response to a cobalt ion stimulus.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to calcium ion

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter in response to a calcium ion stimulus.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to a hypotonic environment

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of detection of, or exposure to, a decrease in the concentration of salt (particularly but not exclusively sodium and chloride ions) in the environment.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to acidic pH

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a pH stimulus with pH -lt- 7.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to nitrosative stress

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a nitrosative stress stimulus. Nitrosative stress is a state often resulting from exposure to high levels of nitric oxide (NO) or the highly reactive oxidant peroxynitrite, which is produced following interaction of NO with superoxide anions.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to increased salt

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of detection of, or exposure to, an increase in the concentration of salt (particularly but not exclusively sodium and chloride ions) in the environment.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to hydrostatic pressure

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a hydrostatic pressure stimulus. Hydrostatic pressure is the force acting on an object in a system where the fluid is at rest (as opposed to moving). The weight of the fluid above the object creates pressure on it.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to glucose starvation

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of deprivation of glucose.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to hydrogen peroxide

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a hydrogen peroxide (H2O2) stimulus.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to heat stress

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a heat stimulus, a temperature stimulus above the optimal temperature for that organism.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to freezing

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a freezing stimulus, temperatures below 0 degrees Celsius.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to ethanol

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of an ethanol stimulus.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to cold

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a cold stimulus, a temperature stimulus below the optimal temperature for that organism.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to amino acid starvation

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of deprivation of amino acids.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter by a nonfermentable carbon source

definition.value: A transcription regulation process in which the presence of a nonfermentable carbon source leads to the modulation of the frequency, rate, or extent of transcription, from an RNA polymerase II promoter, of specific genes involved in the metabolism of other carbon sources.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter by a nonfermentable carbon source

definition.value: A transcription regulation process in which the presence of a nonfermentable carbon source leads to an increase of the frequency, rate, or extent of transcription, from an RNA polymerase II promoter, of specific genes involved in the metabolism of other carbon sources.

label.value: negative regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter by a nonfermentable carbon source

definition.value: A transcription regulation process in which the presence of a nonfermentable carbon source leads to a decrease of the frequency, rate, or extent of transcription, from an RNA polymerase II promoter, of specific genes involved in the metabolism of other carbon sources.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to salt stress

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a stimulus indicating the organism is under salt stress. The stress is usually an increase or decrease in the concentration of salt (particularly but not exclusively sodium and chloride ions) in the environment.

label.value: negative regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to oxidative stress

definition.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a stimulus indicating the organism is under oxidative stress, a state often resulting from exposure to high levels of reactive oxygen species, e.g. superoxide anions, hydrogen peroxide (H2O2), and hydroxyl radicals.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to hypoxia

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a hypoxia stimulus.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to hypoxia

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a hypoxia stimulus.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to biotin starvation

definition.value: Modulation of the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of deprivation of biotin.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription by oleic acid

definition.value: Any process involving oleic acid that activates or increases the rate of transcription.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to alkaline pH

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a pH -gt-7.0.

label.value: positive regulation of sodium ion transport by positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter resulting in the increased frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of sodium ions (Na+) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label.value: positive regulation of peroxisome organization by positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter and activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of peroxisome organization.
